  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Forming a quadratic expression from increasing dimensions</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A rectangular playground has length \((x + {@a@})\) metres and width \(x\) metres. The width is increased by {@b@} metres.
</p>
<p>
Form and simplify an expression for the new area of the playground.
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Original length = \(x + {@a@}\)
</p>

<p>
Original width = \(x\)
</p>

<p>
After the increase, the new width is:
</p>

<p>
\[
x + {@b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Area = length × width
</p>

<p>
\[
(x + {@a@})(x + {@b@})
\]
</p>

<p>
Multiply each term in the first bracket by each term in the second bracket:
</p>

<p>
\[
x(x + {@b@}) + {@a@}(x + {@b@})
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= x^2 + {@b@}x + {@a@}x + {@a*b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Combine like terms:
</p>

<p>
\[
= x^2 + {@a + b@}x + {@a*b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the new area in simplest form is:
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + {@a + b@}x + {@a*b@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
